            <title>[KAFKA-14078] Replica fetches to follower should return NOT_LEADER error</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-14078</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;After the fix for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-13837&quot; title=&quot;Return error for Fetch requests from unrecognized followers&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-13837&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-13837&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, if a follower receives a request from another replica, it will return UNKNOWN_LEADER_EPOCH even if the leader epoch matches. We need to do epoch leader/epoch validation first before we check whether we have a valid replica.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
